divs: sighting detailsi was conducting a land survey when i noticed the object today (oct. 27\10) between 10-10:30am and which was viewed flying north from my position on grove road, about 1-2 miles north of rt. 126. the object caught my eye because it seemed to be moving rather fast, and it also made no sound whatsoever. it seemed odd for some reason, so i attempted to take a couple of photos of it. i had trouble finding it in the view master of the camera because of the time of day, and also trying to find something so small is like the proverbial needle in a haystack. anyways, i later loaded the photos onto my computer. at first i thought i had totally missed it, but then on one shot, i saw that i did indeed capture it. it is not a great shot, but it may still prove important. it is a white cylindrical object just above the tips of the leaves on the trees near the lower middle portion of the frame. when magnified, the object appears to be mainly white with a dark band around its middle and one end dark. in the direction of travel, the dark tip is leading the rest of the craft. but most important of all, it appears to have no wings at all. although it was an exceptionally windy day out there today, this was not floating debris. i had watched the thing fly in a perfectly level (from my vantage point) tragectory for several seconds, an impossibility if it was a floating piece of paper or a bag of some kind. i eventually lost sight of the object against the blue sky and the brightness of the day.
